     1â†’## Usage
     3â†’Those templates dependencies are maintained via [pnpm](https://pnpm.io) via `pnpm up -Lri`.
     4â†’
     5â†’This is the reason you see a `pnpm-lock.yaml`. That being said, any package manager will work. This file can be safely be removed once you clone a template.
     6â†’
     7â†’```bash
     8â†’$ npm install # or pnpm install or yarn install
     9â†’```
    10â†’
    11â†’### Learn more on the [Solid Website](https://solidjs.com) and come chat with us on our [Discord](https://discord.com/invite/solidjs)
    13â†’## Available Scripts
    15â†’In the project directory, you can run:
    16â†’
    17â†’### `npm run dev` or `npm start`
    19â†’Runs the app in the development mode.<br>
    20â†’Open [http://localhost:3000](http://localhost:3000) to view it in the browser.
    21â†’
    22â†’The page will reload if you make edits.<br>
    23â†’
    24â†’### `npm run build`
    26â†’Builds the app for production to the `dist` folder.<br>
    27â†’It correctly bundles Solid in production mode and optimizes the build for the best performance.
    28â†’
    29â†’The build is minified and the filenames include the hashes.<br>
    30â†’Your app is ready to be deployed!
    31â†’
    32â†’## Deployment
    34â†’You can deploy the `dist` folder to any static host provider (netlify, surge, now, etc.)
    35â†’
    36â†’## This project was created with the [Solid CLI](https://solid-cli.netlify.app)

